1. ## 🔹 Spark Streaming
### ✅ Definition
“In Apache Spark, Spark Streaming is a stream processing framework used to process live data streams in near real-time by dividing 
incoming data into small batches and processing them using Spark.”
---
### 🧠 Simple Scenario
👉 Live data coming from:
* Kafka
* Logs
* Sensors
* Transactions

Instead of waiting for end-of-day batch:
Incoming data every second
→ collect small batch
→ process
→ output
```
### 💻 Example
```python id="spark_streaming_ex"
df = spark.readStream.format("kafka").load()
df.writeStream \
  .format("console") \
  .start()
``
---
### ⚙️ How it works
Incoming Stream
   ↓
Micro-batches
   ↓
Spark Processing
   ↓
Output Sink
```
---
### ⚡ Types
#### 🔹 Legacy Spark Streaming
* DStreams (older API)
#### 🔹 Structured Streaming (modern)
* DataFrame/SQL based ✔ preferred
---

### 🎤 Interview Answer
👉
“Spark Streaming is a near real-time stream processing system that processes incoming data as micro-batches. 
Modern Spark uses Structured Streaming, which provides a DataFrame-based streaming API.”
