2.
In Apache Spark, batch processing handles stored data in large chunks at scheduled times, while streaming processes continuously arriving data in near real-time.

| Feature  | Batch               | Streaming              |
| -------- | ------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Data     | Historical / stored | Continuous incoming    |
| Timing   | Scheduled           | Continuous             |
| Latency  | Minutes / hours     | Seconds / milliseconds |
| Use Case | Reports, ETL        | Alerts, live analytics |


3.
🔹 Structured Streaming
✅ Definition

“In Apache Spark, Structured Streaming is Spark’s scalable stream processing engine that treats incoming live data as an unbounded DataFrame and 
allows processing it using the same DataFrame and SQL APIs used for batch data.”

🧠 Simple Scenario

👉 Live transactions are coming continuously from Apache Kafka

Instead of writing separate streaming logic:

Incoming records
→ DataFrame transformations
→ Aggregation
→ Output

Live Data
   ↓
Micro-batches / continuous processing
   ↓
DataFrame / SQL operations
   ↓
Sink (Kafka, file, DB, console)
